<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B65165478E8F96823EDF8D1" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B65165478E8F96823EDF8D1" blockId="21.[136,1452,1634,2093]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B65165478E8F96826D7F96D" bold="true" box="[189,397,1706,1732]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B65165479FCF968256CF96D" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[425,566,1706,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B65165479FCF968256CF96D" box="[425,566,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Sida spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to section 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6516547B52F9692348F96C" authority="(Fryxell 1985)" baseAuthorityName="Fryxell" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[775,1042,1706,1733]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Spinosae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6516547B52F9692436F96C" box="[775,876,1707,1733]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Spinosae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6516547B2CF9682350F96C" author="Fryxell, P. A." box="[889,1034,1706,1733]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" pagination="62 - 91" refId="ref18743" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1985) The North and Central American species of Sida. Sida, Contributions to Botany 11: 62 - 91." type="journal article" year="1985">Fryxell 1985</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B6516547C4AF968232BF96D" box="[1055,1137,1706,1732]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
). One of its striking features is the presence of a small projection, tubercle, such as a spine, but not sharp, in the base of petioles. This feature can also be found in 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B651654791DF9302689F8A5" authorityName="K. Schumann" authorityYear="1891" box="[328,467,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riedelii">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B651654791DF9302689F8A5" box="[328,467,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Sida riedelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a very similar species, that is distinguished by the hyaline and crumbly dorsal face of its mericarps (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B651654797EF8D426BCF899" author="Schumann, K." box="[299,486,1814,1840]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" pagination="253 - 456" refId="ref20394" refString="Schumann, K. (1891) Malvaceae I. In: Martius, C. F. P. de, Eichler, A. G. &amp; Urban, I. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, Vol. 12, pars III. Frid. Fleischer, Lipsiae, pp. 253 - 456, pl. 51 - 80." type="book chapter" year="1891">Schumann 1891</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B65165479A0F8D4259DF898" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[501,711,1814,1841]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" pagination="292 - 333" refId="ref19401" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2005) Malvaceae. In: Bacigalupo, N. M. (Ed.) Flora Ilustrada de Entre-Rios. 6 (4 b). Colecc. Ci. Inst. Nac. Tecnol. Agropecu, pp. 292 - 333." type="book chapter" year="2005">Krapovickas 2005</bibRefCitation>
), vs. mericarps with complete and reticulated dorsal face, which does not easily break (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B65165479D5F8F82574F8FD" box="[384,558,1850,1876]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="22.[136,229,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,190,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[177,1411,190,1932]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 11. A–D. Sida rubifolia. A. Flower. B. Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Prostrate habit. D. Calyx and corolla. E–K. Sida spinosa. E. Flower. F. Abaxial surface of leaf. G. Adaxial surface of leaf. H. Habit. I. Mature schizocarp. J. Branch with tubercle at petiole base. K. Branch. L–Q. Sida tuberculata. L. Branch with leaves, mature and immature schizocarps. M. Adaxial surface of leaf. N. Abaxial surface of leaf. O. Mature schizocarps. P. Branch with flower. Q. Habit. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415511/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Figures 11E–K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6516547A6CF8F8253DF8FD" box="[569,615,1850,1876]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">14S</figureCitation>
). The species 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6516547B51F8F824E6F8FD" authorityName="R. E. Fries" authorityYear="1908" box="[772,956,1850,1876]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6516547B51F8F824E6F8FD" box="[772,956,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Sida tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also present a tubercle at the base of the petioles, which are generally smaller. However, 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6516547AF6F89C2406F8D1" authorityName="R. E. Fries" authorityYear="1908" box="[675,860,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6516547AF6F89C2406F8D1" box="[675,860,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Sida tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has more than five mericarps.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B65165478E8F84023A5F785" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B65165478E8F84023A5F785" blockId="21.[136,1452,1634,2093]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B65165478E8F84025ADF835" bold="true" box="[189,759,1922,1948]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—This species is pantropical, and also occurs in adjacent temperate zones (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B651654791BF86426BEF868" author="Fryxell, P. A." box="[334,484,1958,1985]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" pagination="62 - 91" refId="ref18743" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1985) The North and Central American species of Sida. Sida, Contributions to Botany 11: 62 - 91." type="journal article" year="1985">Fryxell 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B65165479A5F86525B8F868" author="Fuertes Aguilar, J." box="[496,738,1958,1985]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" refId="ref18839" refString="Fuertes Aguilar, J. (1995) Sida L. (Malvaceae). In: Piedrahita, S. D., Telleria, M. T., Castroviejo, S., Mejia, W. J., Carranza, P. R., Contreras, G. L. (Eds.) Flora de Colombia, No. 17. Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota, 142 pp." type="book" year="1995">Fuertes Aguilar 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6516547ABBF864248EF869" author="Brandao, J. L. &amp; Baracho, G. S. &amp; De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V." box="[750,980,1958,1984]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" pagination="205 - 227" refId="ref18144" refString="Brandao, J. L., Baracho, G. S., De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V. (2017) Synopsis of Sida (Malvaceae, Malvoideae, Malveae) in the state of Pernambuco, Brazil. Phytotaxa 307 (3): 205 - 227. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 307.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Brandão 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6516547B00F86524D5F869" box="[853,911,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6516547C52F8642311F869" box="[1031,1099,1958,1984]" name="Brazil" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Brazil</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6516547C06F865239DF869" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1107,1223,1959,1985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6516547C06F865239DF869" box="[1107,1223,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">S. spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in northeast, southeast, midwest and south (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B65165479B9F8082524F84D" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[492,638,1994,2020]" pageId="21" pageNumber="126" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
) and in all regions of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B6516547BD3F80823C4F84C" box="[902,1182,1994,2021]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Rio Grande do Sul state</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6516547CE5F8082279F84D" box="[1200,1315,1994,2020]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="20.[136,229,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[266,1345,252,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-25@20.[204,1384,190,1932]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 10. Distribution map of Sida spinosa and S. rhombifolia in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415509/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="126">Figure 10</figureCitation>
), in ruderal environments and anthropized grasslands, except in Coastal grassland. The species is here considered Least Concern (LC) because it has large EOO and AOO, since it is a frequent and ruderal species, widely distributed.
</paragraph>
